de.iabg.j3d
Interface Renderable

All Known Subinterfaces:
MeshConnectionModel, MeshModel, ModeCorrelationModel
All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultMeshConnectionModel, DefaultMeshModel, JMeshConnectionPanel, JMeshPanel, JModeCorrelationPanel, JModeCorrelationTabbedPane, ModalAssuranceCriterionModel, OrthogonalityCheckModel
public interface Renderable

This interface declares basic functionality for an object that can be rendered in Java3D. The use of listeners allows the Renderer to update the scene based on scene events. Although the rendering will be displayed in 3D, there are instances where a 2D representation of the object is useful. Therefore, this interface declares methods necessary to render a planar 2D scene in Java3D as well. Typically, a Renderer will register listeners on a Renderable object and listen for events. The Renderer will then call the appropriate method to get the scene of the fired source.

Version:
September 10, 2008
Author:
Adam C. Dick, BSE

addSceneListener

void addSceneListener(SceneListener listener)

Parameters:

fireScene2DChanged

void fireScene2DChanged(java.lang.Object source)
Sends a SceneEvent, whose source is this object, to each listener. This method reports that a 2D scene, rather than 3D scene, should be rendered. There may be instances when multiple Renderable objects are aggregated, so a reference of the given source is also sent.

Parameters:
source - the object to be rendered in 2D

fireScene3DChanged

Parameters:
source - the object to be rendered in 3D

getBoundingRadius2D

getScene2D

javax.media.j3d.BranchGroup getScene2D(double scale,
                                       javax.vecmath.Color3f backgroundColor)
Creates a 2D rendering of a Java3D scene that this object represents at the given scale and with the given background color. If there is no scene present, only the background should be created with the given background color.

Parameters:
scale - the scale of the scene
backgroundColor - the background color of the scene
Returns:
a branch group containing the background and the scene that this object represents
